From 4eb5c052e608b38e1f5dd3e1b800535f1ce4e5cf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Emergent Agent <agent@emergent.sh>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 04:45:22 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix TestFlight crash: disable new arch + add error boundary +
 harden init

The v1.0.0 (build 2) TestFlight build crashed on launch with signature:
  EXC_CRASH (SIGABRT) on expo.controller.errorRecoveryQueue
  Last exception: -[NSException raise] -> _objc_terminate -> abort

Root cause: newArchEnabled=true on iOS 26.5 + SDK 54 + reanimated 4 +
keyboard-controller triggers an unrecoverable JS init failure in release
builds, which the Expo native recovery queue surfaces as an uncaught
NSException, terminating the process.

Fixes:
1. app.json: newArchEnabled false (most impactful, lowest risk)
2. Added RootErrorBoundary so any future JS error shows a recoverable UI
   instead of bubbling to the native error-recovery queue
3. Wrapped each startup side effect (SplashScreen.hideAsync, getGuestIdentity,
   initAuth, handleGoogleReturnFromUrl, probeMe) in try/catch so a single
   failure can never abort the process
